### Test Reservation API - Fixed Authentication

### 1. Login to get fresh JWT token
POST https://localhost:7035/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Create Reservation (replace YOUR_NEW_TOKEN with token from step 1)
POST https://localhost:7035/api/reservations
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_NEW_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pointId": 1,
  "startTime": "2025-10-19T05:19:41.956Z",
  "durationMinutes": 60
}

### 3. Get My Reservations
GET https://localhost:7035/api/reservations/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_NEW_TOKEN

### 4. Get Upcoming Reservations
GET https://localhost:7035/api/reservations/upcoming?hours=48
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_NEW_TOKEN

### 5. Generate QR Code (replace {id} with actual reservation ID from step 3)
GET https://localhost:7035/api/reservations/1/qrcode
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_NEW_TOKEN

### 5b. Test QR Code with different reservation ID
GET https://localhost:7035/api/reservations/999/qrcode
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_NEW_TOKEN

### 6. Cancel Reservation (replace {id} with actual reservation ID)
DELETE https://localhost:7035/api/reservations/1?reason=Change of plans
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_NEW_TOKEN
